<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="496" pageId="4" pageNumber="495" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1931,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="495">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1931,1956]" pageId="4" pageNumber="495">Description.</emphasis>
Color pattern of head, scutellum, eyes and ocelli as in 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1057,1932,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Decursusnirvana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsa">
<emphasis box="[939,1057,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="495">D. excelsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but pronotum black with a pale yellow horizontal stripe in the middle (Figs. 
<number box="[661,705,1967,1992]" pageId="4" pageNumber="495" value="2.5">2, 5</number>
), face black (Fig. 
<number box="[915,930,1968,1992]" pageId="4" pageNumber="495" value="8.0">8</number>
), forewing mostly black with two wide pale yellow stripes along anterior margin and claval suture extending to costal margin respectively (Figs. 
<number box="[1278,1322,2003,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="495" value="2.5">2, 5</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">
Shape of male pygofer similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[579,697,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Decursusnirvana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsa">
<emphasis box="[579,697,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">D. excelsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but without ventral process and median lobe not protruded (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1700,1722]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,633,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1408,628,1679]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Decursusnirvana fasciiformis sp. nov. 20, male pygofer, lateral view; 21, subgenital plate, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, connective, dorsal view; 24, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229228/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate, style and connective as in 
<taxonomicName box="[695,813,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Decursusnirvana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsa">
<emphasis box="[695,813,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">D. excelsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[828,1009,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1700,1722]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,633,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1408,628,1679]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Decursusnirvana fasciiformis sp. nov. 20, male pygofer, lateral view; 21, subgenital plate, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, connective, dorsal view; 24, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229228/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">
Figs. 
<number box="[892,1009,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" value="22.615000000000002" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="21.23">21, 23–24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft process similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Decursusnirvana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excelsa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">D. excelsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with pair of subterminal appendages hooklike, not straight and shaft in lateral view thicker (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1404,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1700,1722]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,633,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[180,1408,628,1679]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 24. Decursusnirvana fasciiformis sp. nov. 20, male pygofer, lateral view; 21, subgenital plate, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, lateral view; 23, connective, dorsal view; 24, style, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229228/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">
Fig. 
<number box="[1372,1404,224,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,1137,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="496">Measurements.</emphasis>
Body length (including tegmen): Male 4.9mm, female 5.1–5.5mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
